          <Comment>The Cys41fs variant in LAMP2 has not been reported in individuals with cardiomyo pathy or Danon disease or in large population studies. This frameshift variant i s predicted to alter the protein?s amino acid sequence beginning at position 41 and lead to a premature termination codon 8 amino acids downstream. This alterat ion is then predicted to lead to a truncated or absent protein. Loss of function of the LAMP2 gene is an established disease mechanism in males with Danon disea se. In summary, this variant meets our criteria to be classified as pathogenic ( http://pcpgm.partners.org/LMM) based upon the predicted impact to the protein.</Comment>
